To setup a notewise development environment:

Checkout from svn:

svn co svn+ssh://notewise.com/home/advanced/notewise/svn/trunk notewise

Install the following perl modules:

    Bundle::Catalyst
    Catalyst::Plugin::Authentication::CDBI
    Catalyst::Plugin::FormValidator
    Catalyst::View::TT
    Class::DBI
    Class::DBI::mysql
    Class::DBI::FromForm
    Class::DBI::AsForm
    Class::DBI::Plugin::Type
    Class::DBI::AbstractSearch
    YAML
    DateTime
    DateTime::Format::DateParse
    DateTime::Format::MySQL
    Test::XML
    Test::WWW::Mechanize
    Test::WWW::Mechanize::Catalyst
    Data::Dumper
    Test::More
    XML::Simple
    Catalyst::View::REST::XML
    Module::Install

    You can install perl modules by running:

    sudo perl -MCPAN -eshell
    > install Module::Name
    
Create a new mysql database:

    mysql -uroot -p -e 'create database notewise'

Import the database schema:

    mysql -uroot -p notewise < createTablesMySql.sql

Create a test user and starting kernel:
    mysql -uroot -p notewise
    > insert into user (id,name,email,password) values (1,'Your Name','youremail@notewise.com','password');
    > insert into object_id values (1,1,'kernel');
    > insert into kernel (id, name) values (1,'start');

Copy config-sample.yml to config.yml and edit as appropriate.

	set Static to 1
	set Debig to 1
	set BaseUrl to / or the hostname where things will be loaded

Run 'script/notewise_server.pl -k -r' to test the application.  The default port number is 3000.  To change the port number, use 'script/notewise_server.pl -k -r -p 3005'.


To run the command line unit tests, do:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make test
